msgctxt "1||onomichi||text"
msgid "Onomichi\r\n\r\nA small port town in Hiroshima Prefecture in the south of Japan,\r\nOnomichi is famous for its unique style of ramen. It is also known\r\nfor the great number of traditional temples in and around the town\r\nand carved stones engraved with Onomichi-related poems, originally\r\npenned by various famous Japanese authors."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "2||aniki||text"
msgid "Aniki\r\n \r\nA term that roughly translates to \"big brother,\" often used in\r\ndeference to a more senior member of a yakuza organization."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "3||shun_akiyama||text"
msgid "Shun Akiyama\r\n \r\nFounder of Sky Finance, a Kamurocho-based loan company that\r\nearned him the nickname \"The Lifeline of Kamurocho.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "4||new_serena||text"
msgid "New Serena\r\n\r\nThe second coming of the Serena bar, which closed after the death\r\nof its original owner, Reina. One of Kiryu and Date's usual haunts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "5||tgs||text"
msgid "This demo represents a work in-progress.\r\nFinal version is subject to change."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "6||hiroshima_prefecture||text"
msgid "Hiroshima Prefecture\r\n\r\nNamed for its capital city meaning \"broad island,\" this region of Japan\r\nis known for its oysters, ocean views, rolling mountains, and its\r\nbaked treat, the \"momiji manju,\" a type of steamed bun.\r\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "7||the_omi_alliance||text"
msgid "The Omi Alliance\r\n\r\nThe reigning yakuza faction in the Kansai region, based in\r\nSotenbori, Osaka. Their power rivals that of the Tojo Clan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "8||the_tojo_clan||text"
msgid "The Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nThe reigning yakuza faction over the Kanto region, based in Tokyo.\r\nWith its senior members in prison, its grip on the territory is waning."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "9||chairman||text"
msgid "Chairman\r\n\r\nThe topmost figure of an entire yakuza organization.\r\nDaigo Dojima currently serves as the Tojo Clan's sixth chairman."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "10||patriarch||text"
msgid "Patriarch\r\n\r\nThe head of a yakuza family, a single group in a yakuza organization."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "11||captain||text"
msgid "Captain\r\n\r\nA rank reserved for the right-hand man of a patriarch.\r\nCaptains of larger families often have their own sub-families."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "12||lieutenant_advisor||text"
msgid "Lieutenant Advisor\r\n\r\nA higher-ranking lieutenant, given this term because he has the\r\near of the captain."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "13||lieutenant||text"
msgid "Lieutenant\r\n\r\nAn officer of a family with influence over the day-to-day operation and\r\ncollections. Some lieutenants have sub-families of their own."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "14||family||text"
msgid "Family\r\n\r\nA general term for a single yakuza unit, large or small,\r\nled by a patriarch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "15||the_dragon_of_dojima||text"
msgid "The Dragon of Dojima\r\n\r\nThough the Dojima Family itself has long-since faded from existence,\r\nthe dragon on Kiryu's back earned him this nickname, now legendary\r\namong yakuza across Japan."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "16||yakuza_the_meaning||text"
msgid "Yakuza - The Meaning\r\n\r\nThe word comes from a losing hand in the gambling game oicho-kabu\r\nand came to be associated with those lost to gambling. Yakuza\r\nthemselves prefer a word with a more righteous connotation: \"gokudo.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "17||chinpira||text"
msgid "Chinpira\r\n\r\nA word that translates roughly to \"punk,\" used to describe\r\nlow-level yakuza or the street thugs who pick fights with Kiryu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "18||kyodai||text"
msgid "Kyodai\r\n\r\nWhen yakuza swear their oath, they often do so in pairs, tying their\r\nfates to one another as sworn brothers. It follows that if one succeeds,\r\nso does the other, and if one fails, the other is brought down with him."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "19||history_of_the_tojo_clan_1||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nDetails are scant about the founder of the Tojo Clan, Makoto Tojo,\r\nbut it is said he enjoyed Japanese gardens and was known for his\r\npack of vicious dogs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "20||history_of_the_tojo_clan_2||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nWith the death of Makoto Tojo and no captain to replace him, Takashi\r\nNihara stepped in as acting second chairman. The clan secured the\r\nKamurocho Revitalization Project in 1988 under his leadership."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "21||history_of_the_tojo_clan_3||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nNot long after his promotion to clan captain, Masaru Sera became\r\nthe third chairman. His political ties led to an era of prosperity, but\r\nwhen ten billion yen turned up missing, he was assassinated in 2005."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "22||history_of_the_tojo_clan_4||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nWith the Tojo Clan in civil war, the fourth chairman was named in the\r\nwill of Masaru Sera: Kazuma Kiryu. He was inducted and retired from\r\nthe role on the same day."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "23||history_of_the_tojo_clan_5||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nKazuma Kiryu passed the chairmanship to the fifth chairman, Yukio\r\nTerada. But Terada was compromised in a way that nearly led to\r\nwar with the Jingweon Mafia and the Omi Alliance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "24||history_of_the_tojo_clan_6||text"
msgid "History of the Tojo Clan\r\n\r\nWithout a chairman in 2006, the Tojo Clan was held together by\r\nOsamu Kashiwagi and Sohei Dojima's widow, Yayoi Dojima, until her\r\nson, Daigo Dojima, became the sixth chairman at Kiryu's insistence."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "25||the_jingweon_mafia||text"
msgid "The Jingweon Mafia\r\n\r\nA Korean crime syndicate that was all but eradicated by the Dojima\r\nFamily in the early 80s but resurfaced in 2006 in a plot to destroy \r\nthe entire Tojo Clan. They were pushed back by Kazuma Kiryu and\r\nhis allies."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "26||the_jingweon_massacre||text"
msgid "The Jingweon Massacre\r\n\r\nIn the early 1980s, two members of the Dojima Family ambushed\r\nthis Korean mafia syndicate, killing nearly every member of its\r\nranks. The Jingweon never forgot and never forgave."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "27||poem_stones||text"
msgid "Poem Stones\r\n\r\nInspired by Onomichi's natural beauty, many famous poets have had\r\ntheir verses inscribed on the stones dotting the streets. Pause for\r\na moment and read them if you spot one."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "28||the_ropeway||text"
msgid "The Ropeway\r\n\r\nWhile visiting Onomichi, one would be remiss not to ride\r\nthe ropeway on their trip up the hillside to Senkoji Temple.\r\nMost who visit choose to ride up and walk back down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "29||ono_michio||text"
msgid "Ono Michio\r\n\r\nJapanese citizens are instilled with pride in their cities by colorful\r\nmascot characters, representing a city's unique culture in various\r\nways. Ono Michio is kind of unofficial."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "30||seto_inner_sea||text"
msgid "Seto Inner Sea\r\n\r\nThis body of water is nestled between Honshu and Shikoku, providing \r\nsafe harbor from seasonal typhoons. It has a long history and \r\nculture based around shipbuilding and fishing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "31||mikan||text"
msgid "Mikan\r\n\r\nA favorite winter treat in western Japan, the mikan is a small, easy-to-peel\r\nvariety of tangerine. They are plentiful on the islands off the shore of \r\nOnomichi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "32||onomichi_ramen||text"
msgid "Onomichi Ramen\r\n\r\nEvery region of Japan has its own style of noodles, and Onomichi is\r\nno different. This ramen is notable for its straight noodles and bits\r\nof pork fat floating in soy-sauce-based broth."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "33||jingaicho_onomichi||text"
msgid "Jingaicho, Onomichi\r\n\r\nQuiet streets lined by the softly glowing signs of snack bars, \r\nJingaicho is home to numerous dives that service the locals.\r\nOften run by a single \"mama,\" they cater to clientele looking for\r\na drink and a conversation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "34||senkoji_temple||text"
msgid "Senkoji Temple\r\n\r\nSaid to have been established over 1200 years ago, this temple is\r\nperched on a hill overlooking Onomichi and has been the \r\nsubject of artists and writers since times immemorable."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "35||hiroshima_oysters||text"
msgid "Hiroshima Oysters\r\n\r\nCaught fresh out of the Seto Inner Sea, Hiroshima \"kaki\" are known\r\nthroughout the country as being some of the finest.\r\n\r\n"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "36||jingaicho_central_shopping_district||text"
msgid "Jingaicho Central Shopping District\r\n\r\nOnce a bustling market during the boom years, this local shopping\r\nalley now sits quietly with many of the storefronts shuttered."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "37||haruka_sawamura||text"
msgid "Haruka Sawamura\r\n\r\nThe daughter of Kiryu's first love, Yumi Sawamura. The two met in\r\n2005 and a father-daughter relationship bloomed as Kiryu risked his\r\nlife to protect hers."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "38||daigo_dojima||text"
msgid "Daigo Dojima\r\n\r\nThe sixth chairman of the Tojo Clan, inducted in 2006. Daigo's road to\r\nleadership has been rocky, but Kiryu has supported him since he was\r\na child."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "39||makoto_date||text"
msgid "Makoto Date\r\n\r\nOnce in charge of Kiryu's murder case in 1995, the two became friends\r\nafter his release. Date has been a cop, a journalist, and a bartender,\r\nbut police work runs in his blood."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "40||shintaro_kazama||text"
msgid "Shintaro Kazama\r\n\r\nThe founder of Sunflower Orphanage, where both Kiryu and Haruka\r\ngrew up. He was a model yakuza, earning the trust and respect of the\r\nentire city. Kiryu considered him a father."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "41||akira_nishikiyama||text"
msgid "Akira Nishikiyama\r\n\r\nOnce Kiryu's oath brother, the two were torn apart by Nishiki's ambition\r\nto claim the Tojo Clan chairmanship. Their relationship ended in blows\r\nand an explosion atop the Millennium Tower."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "42||goro_majima||text"
msgid "Goro Majima\r\n\r\nKnown as the Mad Dog of Shimano, his unpredictable nature\r\nhas made him a force to be reckoned with both in the Tojo\r\nClan and to Kiryu, his long-time friend and nemesis."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "43||taiga_saejima||text"
msgid "Taiga Saejima\r\n\r\nOnce sentenced to death row for the murder of 18 men, this massive\r\nman became a yakuza legend. After clearing his name, Saejima has\r\nbeen in and out of prison, escaping whenever the need arises."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "44||the_snake_flower_triad||text"
msgid "The Snake Flower Triad\r\n\r\nOnce a prominent foreign crime organization in Kamurocho, they lost\r\ntheir footing after their leader, Lau Ka Long, was killed by the CIA."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "45||club_stardust||text"
msgid "Club Stardust\r\n\r\nOnce owned by Kazuki and Yuya, close friends of Kiryu's, this host\r\nclub has changed ownership and no longer offers Kiryu asylum from\r\nthe busy streets of the city."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "46||morning_glory_orphanage||text"
msgid "Morning Glory Orphanage\r\n\r\nFounded in Okinawa by Kiryu after he retired from the yakuza, this\r\nbeachfront property is home to eight now-teenage orphans."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "47||kamurocho||text"
msgid "Kamurocho\r\n\r\nAn area of Tokyo, this red-light district is home to cabaret clubs,\r\ngambling houses, a thriving nightlife, and all the ills that follow suit."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "48||the_millennium_tower||text"
msgid "The Millennium Tower\r\n\r\nThe pride of Kamurocho, this skyscraper was built on the blood\r\nspilled over an empty lot in the late 80s. When the fighting among\r\nyakuza gets serious, the roof often becomes an arena."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "49||shangri_la||text"
msgid "Shangri-La\r\n\r\nA derelict \"soapland\" that Kiryu and Haruka infiltrated in 2005\r\nto gain crucial information. Goro Majima found him though,\r\ndriving a dump truck through the front doors in an attack."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "50||taxis||text"
msgid "Taxis\r\n\r\nTaxis offer convenient shortcuts to other parts of the city, marked\r\non your map by a car icon. You can also travel between cities\r\nwhen the story allows. Get in from the left side."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "51||green_marks_the_spot||text"
msgid "Green Marks the Spot\n\nDid you know you can create a marker on your map?\nPress <Action=Confirm,UI> on the map to create the marker,\nand a green arrow will appear on your minimap directing you to it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "52||sprinting||text"
msgid "Sprinting\n\nHold <Action=Run,Adventure> to sprint. Best used in short bursts, it's worth noting\nthat sprinting draws more attention from thugs looking for a fight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "53||all_things_in_moderation||text"
msgid "All Things in Moderation\r\n\r\nKiryu has been known to enjoy a good drink, but if you overdo it,\r\nyou'll find it more difficult to walk in a straight line."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "54||jizo_statues||text"
msgid "Jizo Statues\r\n\r\nLining temples and cemeteries across Japan, these small childlike\r\nstatues are said to protect travelers and children."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "55||cabaret_clubs||text"
msgid "Cabaret Clubs\r\n\r\nThese popular nightlife spots are frequented by men looking for a\r\ndrink and a conversation or businessmen taking clients for a fun\r\nnight out. Sometimes negotiations require a woman's touch."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "56||salarymen||text"
msgid "Salarymen\r\n\r\nA term used to describe men who dedicate their lives to a company.\r\nIt can have a derogatory connotation when used to describe a man who\r\nhas lost sight of his individuality or been broken by work-related stress."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "57||before_eating||text"
msgid "Before Eating\r\n\r\nJapanese people often utter the phrase \"itadakimasu\" while clasping their\r\nhands together with a short bow before eating. Originating in Buddhism,\r\nthis practice is grounded in gratitude for the lives of the organisms\r\nabout to be consumed."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "58||yubitsume||text"
msgid "Yubitsume\r\n\r\nThe ritual act of cutting off one's finger in repentance or atonement.\r\nPracticed almost exclusively by the yakuza, it makes it more difficult\r\nto hold a sword, forcing the perpetrator to act more cautiously."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "59||pocket_tissues||text"
msgid "Pocket Tissues\r\n\r\nOften handed out on the streets of Japan, these \"free gifts\" bear\r\nadvertisements and phone numbers for local clubs and hot spots."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "60||onigiri||text"
msgid "Onigiri\r\n\r\nA ball of rice wrapped around various things such as pickled plums, \r\nsalmon, or other delights, \"onigiri\" are a staple of the Japanese diet."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "61||tea||text"
msgid "Tea\r\n\r\nThe quintessential Japanese beverage \"ocha\" comes in many varieties,\r\nsuch as black (oolong), roasted (hoji), rice-infused (genmai), or \r\neven barley (mugi)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "62||vending_machines||text"
msgid "Vending Machines\r\n\r\nThe Japanese \"jido hanbaiki\" is a global marvel, dispensing all sorts of\r\nconsumable delights, from tea to coffee to beer, in hot and cold varieties!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "63||karaoke||text"
msgid "Karaoke\r\n\r\nA popular pastime that has picked up steam even in Western cultures.\r\nGroups of friends can reserve a room with a hot mic and belt out all\r\nthe latest hits and classics."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "64||cat_cafes||text"
msgid "Cat Cafés\r\n\r\nLove cats but can't have one at home? Why not drop by a\r\ncat café and enjoy coffee, sweets, and amorous kitties?"
msgstr ""

